issue.body:
Currently, there are several cases [heapvar_should_move.ql](https://github.com/Lslightly/QLStat/blob/865d74619c8b282c4328bc53e8e52113e9b3cf08/qlsrc/escape_ext/heapvar_should_move.ql) can't handle.

1. `MovedToHeapVar` is referenced by another function which is later called in another goroutine. In [rclone code snippet](https://github.com/rclone/rclone/blob/73bcae2245467725880653db714b936d58ea4f13/backend/drive/drive.go#L2217-L2282), the code can be simplified as 

```go
overflow := []listREntry{}
sendJob := func() {
    overflow = append(overflow, ...)
}
go sendJob()
go func() {
    for _, d := range overflow {
        ...
    }
}()
```

In this case, `sendJob` is a closure function which will reference `overflow` and will be executed in another goroutine. In this case, `overflow` should not be considered as an variable that need to be moved to heap.

2. `MovedToHeapVar` is referenced by a defered statement. In this case, the variable lifetime is defered to the end of the function, which is later than any GoStmt in same block. In [rclone code snippet](https://github.com/rclone/rclone/blob/73bcae2245467725880653db714b936d58ea4f13/cmd/serve/dlna/dlna.go#L509-L517), the code can be simplified as:

```go
defer ssdpServer.Close()
go func() {
    ssdpServer.Serve()
}()
```

In this case, `ssdpServer` shoud not be considered as an variable that need to be moved to heap.

